                <head type="CCC">Stephen Langton, De poenitentia sub persona Magdalenae</head>

                <head type="James">Stephen Langton (?) De penitentia Magdalenae</head>

                <p function="Codicology"><material>Vellum</material>, <measureGrp type="CCC">
                        <height unit="mm">233</height>
                        <width unit="mm">170</width>
                    </measureGrp><measureGrp type="James">9.2 x 6.8</measureGrp>, <extent>ff. 112 + 4</extent>,
                        <layout>30 lines to a page</layout>. Cent. <origDate>xiii</origDate>, <handNote>apparently in
                        the same hand as <ref type="ms" target="CCC222">MS 222</ref>: the flyleaves belonging to it are
                        in that volume</handNote>.</p>

                <p><label>Collation:</label>
                    <collation>3 flyleaves, I<num>8</num>-XV<num>8</num>, 1 flyleaf</collation>.</p>

                <p function="Additions">The flyleaves are from a MS. of sermons (?) in double columns. The name <q>
                        <name type="person">Savanarola</name>
                    </q> is scribbled on the flyleaf; no doubt in consequence of some confusion with <ref type="ms"
                        target="CCC237">MS 237</ref>.</p>

                <p>Marginal references to authorities are given <handNote>in a hand of cent.
                        <date>xiii</date></handNote>: noteworthy is one which occurs several times, <q>philo in libro
                        sapientie</q> as a ref. to the Wisdom of Solomon.</p>

                <p function="Provenance">The text is evidently the Liber de penitentia Magdalenae of which the flyleaves
                    are in <ref type="ms" target="CCC222">MS 222</ref>. This volume therefore is also from <name
                        type="place" key="CanterbChCh">Christ Church, Canterbury</name>. No title is given.</p>

                <p rend="afterContents">The tract is ascribed by <ref type="bibl" target="Bale 1902">Bale</ref> and <ref
                        type="bibl" target="Tanner 1748">Tanner</ref> to <name type="person">Simon Langton</name>, but
                    by <ref type="ms" target="OBC152">Balliol MS. 152</ref>, by <name type="person">Boston of
                        Bury</name>, and also by <ref type="bibl" target="Bale 1902">Bale</ref>, to <name type="person"
                        key="StLa01">Stephen Langton</name>.</p>

                <p type="CCC">
                    <foliation>pp. a-d + ff. i-iii + 1-112 + iv</foliation>.</p>




